(arr[i] - arr[k]) <= c:\n                            count += 1\n                            \n        return count\n```\n\nThis code defines a method `countGoodTriplets` within the `Solution` class. It iterates over all possible triplets `(i, j, k)` in the array `arr` and checks if they satisfy the given conditions. If a triplet satisfies all the conditions, it increments the `count`. Finally, it returns the total count of good triplets.", "estimated_date": 1596326400000}